Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.56,0:00:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So what's new on iOS?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.41,0:00:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For this release, a major theme
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,has been Wayfinding.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.68,0:00:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Wayfinding traditionally
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.97,0:00:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,refers to all the ways that we
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.06,0:00:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,can help guide people through an
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.93,0:00:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,environment and orient
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.61,0:00:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves within a physical
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.89,0:00:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,space.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.95,0:00:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You encounter signage and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.34,0:00:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,information systems everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.14,0:00:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you find your way from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.22,0:00:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,street signs, to airports, and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.97,0:00:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,even in parking garages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.44,0:00:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So naturally, our digital
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.03,0:00:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,environments can benefit from
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.65,0:00:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,clear navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.71,0:00:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Wayfinding in UI can enhance
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.81,0:01:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your experience and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.26,0:01:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of the space that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.46,0:01:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.99,0:01:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when we design for iOS, our
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.32,0:01:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,goal is to highlight content
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.65,0:01:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,first.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But app layouts need clear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.80,0:01:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,visual hierarchy so that people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.67,0:01:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,know how to navigate through the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.04,0:01:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.42,0:01:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,UI elements in general should
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.47,0:01:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not compete with content but
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.42,0:01:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,help you to better understand
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.76,0:01:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,potential functions and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.06,0:01:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,interactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.44,0:01:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we are constantly trying to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.01,0:01:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,improve upon these themes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.72,0:01:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So for iOS 11, we wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.14,0:01:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,provide more clarity for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.33,0:01:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation or Wayfinding
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.25,0:01:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.75,0:01:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to focus on overall
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.18,0:01:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy through the use of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.00,0:01:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,typography.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.35,0:01:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it would be useful, we
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.10,0:01:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to create greater
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.31,0:01:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast by refining elements
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.54,0:01:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,within the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So first, let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.89,0:01:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.40,0:01:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year we started using more
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.03,0:01:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,bold text in music because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.47,0:02:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,an app with a lot of dense
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.79,0:02:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.23,0:02:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Text became instrumental for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.04,0:02:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,organizing similar media and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.04,0:02:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,orienting you while you browse
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.33,0:02:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and search.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And we recognize that other apps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.66,0:02:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,could benefit from the same text
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,treatments.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.60,0:02:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So this year, we introduce large
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,titles to navigation bars for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.93,0:02:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,other apps that could use some
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.55,0:02:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,more emphasis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.50,0:02:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This does not replace our
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.94,0:02:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,standard navigation but is an
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,opt-in version that transitions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,from to the standard Nav bar
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.74,0:02:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,when you start scrolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.87,0:02:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you might be wondering where
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.65,0:02:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,these large titles should be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.18,0:02:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,used and I can highlight a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,couple guidelines to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.02,0:02:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that we found helpful when
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.61,0:02:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,deciding which of our apps
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.05,0:02:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd be most appropriate for.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A good place to use large-title
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.46,0:02:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation can be at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.41,0:02:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,level of an app with tabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.95,0:02:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This helps to understand that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.22,0:02:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you're at a top level but also
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.09,0:02:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're scrolled to the top
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of the page.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.39,0:02:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, music is a good example
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.61,0:03:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of an app that uses large titles
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of its top levels but
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.22,0:03:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,also occasionally on some
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.17,0:03:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,secondary levels or further
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.76,0:03:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.25,0:03:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Since music has so much content
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.54,0:03:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and multiple levels that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.93,0:03:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,drill into, large titles are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.26,0:03:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,helpful as you navigate further
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.06,0:03:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,into the app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.31,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be used for views that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,all have very similar layouts as
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a quick read on where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.73,0:03:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Phone is an appropriate app to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.45,0:03:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,use large titles because almost
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.75,0:03:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the tabs show content in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.31,0:03:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,rows of text.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.05,0:03:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's important to stress
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.48,0:03:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not always necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.27,0:03:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to use large titles in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.71,0:03:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.02,0:03:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that in multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.28,0:03:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,scenarios it would hinder
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.90,0:03:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,usability and not help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.75,0:03:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And a good example of that is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.98,0:03:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the clock app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.31,0:03:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it's an app with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.69,0:03:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,tabs, it doesn't have multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.37,0:03:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,content to sort through and each
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.93,0:04:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the tabs has a very distinct
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.60,0:04:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.72,0:04:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So large titles in this case
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.65,0:04:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,would compete with content.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a closer look at
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.01,0:04:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,ways that we can improve
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy through type.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.92,0:04:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Typographic hierarchy is the way
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.89,0:04:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to organize type in a way that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.91,0:04:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will emphasize important content
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.94,0:04:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,over less important content and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.37,0:04:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it can help to group things
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.85,0:04:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This can reduce cognitive load
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.60,0:04:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or the amount of mental effort
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.53,0:04:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes you to find something
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.97,0:04:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.92,0:04:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are a few basic
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.58,0:04:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,methods for establishing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,typographic hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.69,0:04:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The position of the text can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,convey importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.51,0:04:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Label 1 is on top, we can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,infer that it's more important
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.76,0:04:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,than Label 2, but that might not
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.93,0:04:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,be obvious in all cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.87,0:04:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So another way is to decrease
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.39,0:04:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of the secondary line
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.93,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can vary the weight or
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use color so that the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.08,0:05:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,secondary line recedes more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.51,0:05:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You may need to use more than
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.70,0:05:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,one of these at a time so you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can make sure there's clear
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.33,0:05:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,hierarchy between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.40,0:05:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a screen from photos in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.63,0:05:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.45,0:05:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important information
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.16,0:05:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,here is your content, your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.80,0:05:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The section headers use two text
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.53,0:05:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,sizes to distinguish different
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.89,0:05:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,information but all of it is a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.87,0:05:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,tad small and light.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So for iOS 11, we made section
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,headers larger in general and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.42,0:05:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,increased the text weight and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.51,0:05:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,used gray for supporting text.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.32,0:05:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And these changes made it easier
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.79,0:05:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to isolate important in content
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.72,0:05:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can find a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,particular photo faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.50,0:05:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's look at more examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.96,0:05:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Calendar in iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We increased text weights for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.35,0:05:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,more emphasis and used color
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.24,0:05:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,more intentionally to denote the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.38,0:05:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,current year, month, and date.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is Weather in iOS 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.02,0:06:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,For iOS 11, we increased the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.07,0:06:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,text weights and made the text
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.80,0:06:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,overall larger so that the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.59,0:06:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,content is easier to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So last, let's look at ways that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.02,0:06:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tried to improve contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.81,0:06:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To create more balance with the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.32,0:06:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,larger and more bold text styles
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.52,0:06:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the UI, we needed to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.37,0:06:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,update other UI elements to give
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.41,0:06:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,them greater contrast while
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping them both functional and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.65,0:06:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,minimal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.58,0:06:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the ways we did this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was to fill in the button shapes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.45,0:06:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and increase the size of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,shape itself like we did with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.03,0:06:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the search field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And we updated the tab bars
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.41,0:06:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,increasing the weight of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.48,0:06:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,label from regular to medium.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.26,0:06:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the glyphs, we filled in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the shapes and thickened the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,stroke weights.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.07,0:06:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make better use of space
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in landscape, we moved the label
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.39,0:07:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it's side by side with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.51,0:07:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the glyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.81,0:07:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This tab bar is now shorter than
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,before and now matches the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,landscape Nav bar and toolbar
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,height.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.34,0:07:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And a couple other things to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.13,0:07:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,note are that the glyphs are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.85,0:07:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,slightly smaller and the text is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.59,0:07:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,slightly larger than the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.11,0:07:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,portrait equivalents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.07,0:07:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll want to make sure you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.40,0:07:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,take that into account for your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.04,0:07:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,own apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.36,0:07:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,On iPad, we can increase the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,text size even more while
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping the glyphs the same as
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.24,0:07:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Wallet app from iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.09,0:07:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,10.
